English:
How do you get someone to go out with you?
Why in the world are you asking hackers that?
Chinese:
可以交到女朋友的方法……？
你為什麼要到處問駭客這種事情啊……？
Korean:
여자친구를 만드는 방법…?
왜 그런걸 해커한테 묻고 다니는데…?
German:
Wie man eine Verabredung kriegt?
Warum zum Geier fragst du das denn Hacker?
Äh, wie wär’s denn mit Speed-Dating?

English:
Well, it's all about what happens after the speed
date. Whether it's a hook-up or a flop is up to
you.
Chinese:
唉呀，就算去參加聯誼，
交不交得到女朋友，還是得看本人的能耐就是了。
Korean:
뭐, 미팅한다고 해도
여자친구가 생길지 어떨진 본인하기 나름이지만.
German:
Kommt halt darauf an, was nach dem Speed-Date
passiert. Und das liegt bei dir.

English:
U-uhhh...
I-I guess I'm not against doing it with friends...
--What? You're talking about something different?
Chinese:
喔……
我也不是不能跟你交個朋友啦……
咦？　你不是那個意思？
Korean:
오…그래.
딱히… 친구가 되어주지 못할건 없지만…
응? 그런 이야기가 아니라고?
German:
Ääähm ... Mit Freunden ist es ganz okay ...
Wie? Du redest von was anderem?

English:
Digimon, huh...
I wanna get my hands on some stronger Digimon,
too. Maybe I'll head further into Kowloon...
Chinese:
數碼寶貝嗎……
我也想獲得更強的數碼寶貝啊……
要不要去Kowloon的深處看看呢……
Korean:
디지몬인가아…
나도 더 강한 디지몬을 손에 넣고 싶다…
쿠롱 안쪽에라도 다녀와볼까.
German:
Digimon, hm ...
Ich hätte auch gern ein paar stärkere.
Vielleicht gehe ich mal weiter nach Kowloon rein.
